ref: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.40, p.127 (1989)
title: Excitation functions of proton induced nuclear reactions on natural tellurium and enriched Te-123- production of I-123 via the Te-123(p,n)I-123-process at a low-energy cyclotron.

x4freetext: Excitation functions of proton induced nuclear
reactions on natural tellurium and enriched Te-123-
production of I-123 via the Te-123(p,n)I-123-process

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.40, p.127 (1989)

x4freetext: BIB section upgrated. Correction was done,
DATA-Header and other new Exfor rules.
Each stack consisted of between 5 and 10 sandwiches
(Ti-Te-Al) and several Cu monitor foils (99.9 Per
/By authors/.The total errors in the measured cross
sections were obtained by combining the individual
errors in quadrature. The total errors amounted to
about 12 per cent except for energies near thresholds
of reactions. In the case of Te-123(p,2n)I-122
reaction, due to the short half-live of the product
the errors in cross sections were higher.
